 Summary

 Add font size controls to TipTapEditor component used across blog descriptions, event descriptions, and teaching event content.

 Affected Files

 - frontend/src/components/common/TipTapEditor.tsx - Main editor component

 Current State

 - TipTap editor already has TextStyle extension (required for font size)
 - No font size extension configured
 - Toolbar has color picker pattern we can follow for dropdown UI
 - Used in 7 components (BlogForm, EventModals, BasicInfoTab variants)

 Implementation

 Step 1: Install TipTap Font Size Extension

 cd frontend && npm install @tiptap/extension-font-size

 Note: TipTap doesn't have official font-size extension. We'll use the TextStyle extension (already installed) and create a custom FontSize
 extension or use inline styles via the existing TextStyle.

 Step 2: Add FontSize Extension to TipTapEditor.tsx

 Create custom FontSize extension using TipTap's extension API:

 import { Extension } from '@tiptap/core';

 // Custom FontSize extension
 const FontSize = Extension.create({
   name: 'fontSize',
   addOptions() {
     return {
       types: ['textStyle'],
     };
   },
   addGlobalAttributes() {
     return [
       {
         types: this.options.types,
         attributes: {
           fontSize: {
             default: null,
             parseHTML: element => element.style.fontSize?.replace(/['"]+/g, ''),
             renderHTML: attributes => {
               if (!attributes.fontSize) return {};
               return { style: `font-size: ${attributes.fontSize}` };
             },
           },
         },
       },
     ];
   },
   addCommands() {
     return {
       setFontSize: (fontSize: string) => ({ chain }) => {
         return chain().setMark('textStyle', { fontSize }).run();
       },
       unsetFontSize: () => ({ chain }) => {
         return chain().setMark('textStyle', { fontSize: null }).removeEmptyTextStyle().run();
       },
     };
   },
 });

 Step 3: Add to Editor Extensions Array

 Add FontSize to the useEditor extensions (after TextStyle):

 const editor = useEditor({
   extensions: [
     // ... existing extensions
     TextStyle,
     FontSize,  // Add after TextStyle
