 TipTap Editor Enhancement: WordPress-Style Features

 Current State Summary

 Your TipTap editor already has solid features:
 - Rich text formatting (bold, italic, underline, strikethrough, code)
 - Headings (H1-H3), lists, blockquotes, alignment
 - Tables with add/delete row/col
 - Media insertion (images, videos, YouTube)
 - Color picker, highlight, font size/weight/family
 - HTML insertion modal with built-in CSS classes
 - Character/word count

 ---
 Missing Features (WordPress Comparison)

 1. Visual/Code Mode Toggle ⭐ HIGH PRIORITY

 WordPress has a prominent "Visual" / "Text" tab toggle at the top.

 What's Missing:
 - No way to see/edit raw HTML while staying in editor
 - Current HTML insert is one-way (insert only, can't view existing)
 - No syntax highlighting for HTML code view

 Implementation:
 - Add tab bar: [Visual] [HTML] above toolbar
 - HTML mode: CodeMirror/Monaco editor with syntax highlighting
 - Sync content between modes on tab switch
 - Show line numbers in code mode

 ---
 2. Keyboard Shortcuts Display ⭐ MEDIUM

 WordPress shows shortcuts in tooltips and has a help modal.

 What's Missing:
 - No keyboard shortcut hints in tooltips
 - No shortcuts help modal/panel
 - Users don't know Ctrl+B, Ctrl+I, etc. work

 Implementation:
 - Add shortcut hints to button titles: "Bold (Ctrl+B)"
 - Add ? button that opens shortcuts reference modal

 ---
 3. Distraction-Free / Fullscreen Mode ⭐ MEDIUM

 WordPress has a fullscreen writing mode.

 What's Missing:
 - No fullscreen/focus mode
 - No way to hide surrounding UI while writing

 Implementation:
 - Add fullscreen toggle button (expand icon)
 - Use portal to render editor fullscreen with just toolbar + content
 - ESC key to exit

 ---
 4. Find & Replace ⭐ MEDIUM

 WordPress Classic Editor has find/replace.

 What's Missing:
 - No text search within editor
 - No replace functionality

 Implementation:
 - Add search icon button
 - Popover with: Find input, Replace input, Replace/Replace All buttons
 - Highlight matches in editor

 ---
 5. Special Characters Insert ⭐ LOW

 WordPress has special character picker (©, ™, €, arrows, etc.)

 What's Missing:
 - No way to insert symbols/emojis
 - Users must copy-paste from external sources

 Implementation:
 - Add Ω button opening character picker modal
 - Categories: Symbols, Arrows, Currency, Math, Emojis

 ---
 6. Horizontal Rule / Divider ⭐ LOW

 WordPress has "Insert Horizontal Line" button.

 What's Missing:
 - No <hr> insertion button (must use HTML mode)

 Implementation:
 - Add horizontal rule button
 - TipTap has HorizontalRule extension (just needs enabling)

 ---
 7. Anchor Links / ID Attributes ⭐ LOW

 WordPress allows setting anchor IDs for internal linking.

 What's Missing:
 - No way to set id attributes on headings/blocks
 - Can't create jump-to-section links

 Implementation:
 - Add anchor button when heading selected
 - Prompt for anchor ID
 - Show anchor icon indicator on elements with IDs

 ---
 8. Media Caption Support ⭐ MEDIUM

 WordPress has native image captions.

 What's Missing:
 - Images insert without caption field
 - Must use HTML for <figure> + <figcaption>

 Implementation:
 - Wrap images in <figure> by default
 - Add editable <figcaption> below image
 - Use TipTap's Figure extension or custom node

